Cell["\<\
Because of positional uncertainty, the Bohr model assumption of fixed orbital \
distances cannot be correct. While the Bohr radius is incorrect, the idea of \
energy levels proved to be a valuable one, and in the notebook on quantum \
numbers, the exact use of energy levels will be explored.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9854562532723866`*^9, 3.985456304310791*^9}, {
  3.985456369934141*^9, 3.985456371912155*^9}, {3.9854754955568333`*^9, 
  3.9854755446776714`*^9}, {3.985476112151581*^9, 
  3.985476167303404*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46b5fde1-02ba-0244-84c2-\
ecbec632b58b"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
